{
  "stem": "13483.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think mainly because we didn't want to be recognized as Jews at the time, being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a lot of that-- well, a lot of Jewish-- anti-Semitism was being preached by the British Union of Fascists at the time.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And sometimes, it could have been difficult trying to get a job, or [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] being embarrassed, you know?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I didn't change my name until, actually, I was in the Army.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I thought that if I was going abroad to fight, I didn't want to have the name of Shernovsky, in case I got captured by the Germans, which seems a little unreasonable right now.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But anyway, I did join the Army on 27th of March, 1939.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "During one of my leaves, I married my late wife, which was 12th of July, 1939.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I did home service right till the 3rd of June, 1944.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then left from Harich for D-Day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I landed on Arromanches--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, not too much.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I said, in a very not abstract way, but a very covert way-- covert way, you know?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I would say this party was getting quite strong in Great Britain, the British Union of Fascists.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The present government at the time, which I think was the Baldwin government, seemed to turn a blind eye to this anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was involved in lots of clashes, not personally.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But a Young Communist League and Jewish people were generally assailed with anti-Semitism and snide remarks.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Go back to-- go back to Palestine, Jew boy, Yid, things like that, which-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which was very, very-- what?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Very, very painful at the time, because was only young.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, my father was a kosher butcher.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
